#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:10
msgid ""
":doc:`ROS distributions <../Releases>` do not support end-of-life (EOL) "
"platforms, even if the ROS distribution is still active. This page explains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:13
msgid "What users of EOL platforms should expect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:14
msgid "What ROS Bosses should do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:17
msgid "Policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:19
msgid ""
"Every ROS distribution supports certain **platforms**, such as Windows 11 or "
"Ubuntu 24.04. **Vendors** of these platforms, such as Microsoft or "
"Canonical, decide how long they will support one of their platforms. When a "
"vendor decides a platform has reached EOL, they usually stop publishing "
"critical bug and security fixes. To protect ourselves from potentially "
"unpatched security vulnerabilities, we proactively remove all jobs on EOL "
"platforms from the ROS build farm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:24
msgid ""
"If you are using a platform that is no longer supported by its vendor, you "
"should expect to stop receiving updated ROS packages. Existing ROS packages "
"will remain available and functional, but they will no longer be updated. "
"However, ROS Bosses may choose to update packages on an EOL platform in "
"exceptional circumstances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:29
msgid "For ROS Bosses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:31
msgid "Before a target platform reaches EOL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:33
msgid ""
"Make sure the ROS distribution documentation includes EOL dates for any "
"platform that reaches EOL before the ROS distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:34
msgid ""
"Post an announcement about the platform reaching EOL at least 2 syncs "
"(roughly 60-90 days) beforehand so that package maintainers have time to "
"update their packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:35
msgid ""
"Open a `pull request disabling buildfarm jobs for that platform <https://"
"github.com/ros2/ros_buildfarm_config>`_ and seek review from the "
"`Infrastructure PMC <https://osralliance.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/"
"infrastructure_project_charter.pdf>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:36
msgid "Make one last sync to that platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:38
msgid "After a target platform reaches EOL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:40
msgid ""
"Update the ROS distribution docs to state the platform will not receive "
"updated ROS packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:41
msgid ""
"Announce that the ROS distribution has dropped support for that platform on "
"Discourse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:42
msgid "Consider making one last release to that platform if:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:43
msgid "You did not already do so prior to EOL, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:44
msgid "The updates seem unlikely to have regressions, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:45
msgid "The ROS Buildfarm still has runners for that platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/The-ROS2-Project/Platform-EOL-Policy.rst:46
msgid "Merge your pull request to disable the buildfarm jobs."
msgstr ""
